The naming convention for constructor function starts with uppercase letter and
the rest lowe-case letters.

Note: Functions are also objects. A function's prototype points to/inherits from
Object which is the root object in JavaScript


    function Person(firstname, lastname, age) {
      this.firstname = firstname;
